Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 1:44:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resistance Suits</span><hr size=1> Things not to bother with:<br>
-the blue diamond tiara.  Waste of a blue diamond.  You lose a huge amount of AC ... go with a crown of the froglok kings instead.  Much cheaper, better AC and good resists.  If you have a blue diamond to spare after having your two bracers made, or money to spare after buying the bracers, then it should go to making an earring.<br>
-the blue diamond pendant.  Again, a waste of a blue diamond.  Get a velium wolf's eye agate necklace instead, +14 sv magic.<br>
-about the diamond mask, think hard about whether you want to do gold or electrum (whether you want the +10s to be to fire/cold or poison/disease).  If you only expect to do Vox/Nag, fine, get gold.  If you ever expect to hit any of the poison/disease based dragons in Kunark and Velious, consider getting the electrum one instead; poison and disease resists are considerably harder to get, and need to be considerably higher, than fire and cold for Vox/Nag.  Heck, feel free to get both if you can afford it.<br>
<br>
You may be wondering why a blue diamond would be used to make an earring, which may seem to have not-as-good resists ... the answer is availability of items for that slot.  With neck slot, head slot, etc., there are many other ac/wis/resist/hp/mana items available.  There are relatively few different earrings in the game and they don't have all that great of stats, so you lose very little by substituting in a blue diamond earring for them. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>54 Wanderer, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
