51st level Wanderer, Officer in Troubles Band<BR>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 11:02:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Kalinn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resistance Suits</span><hr size=1> hehehehehe<br>
please remember, blue diamond jewelry is top of the line.  it is the hardest jewelry to make, therefore has a very high failure rate and isnt going to be trivial, even at a skill of 225+.  as you go up in metals (silver, electrum, gold, platinum, velium), the difficulty of making an item, and thus the failure rate, goes up.<br>
blue diamond bracers are the hardest possible to attempt, because they are made with the highest metal, velium.  if you are looking at providing a jeweller with the components to make your items, expect to provide about 4-5 blue diamonds for ONE successful combine on a bracer (and 5 bars of velium at 262pp each).  if you are buying them, bracers run around 10-15k each.<br>
blue diamond earrings are some of the easiest to make, because they use electrum.  they are the most common use of blue diamonds, because their difficulty is so much lower, and their stats are excellent for earrings (+38 to resists in exchange for a commonly 0-3 ac/wis earring).  they also run about 1/4 the cost of a blue diamond bracer.<br>
<br>
if cost is an issue and you definately want to go after player made jewelry, its cheaper to go for specific-resist jewelry, simply because its made with much more common gems and you can get only what you need with higher resist amounts.  rather than pay several k for a diamond ring that gives 8 svall, pay 150p for a 10 sv poison or fire or cold ring.  13 svmagic rings are made with plat and jacinth and are also much cheaper, even if running around 400 or 500p.  you generally have to carry more gear since its resist specific, but its cheaper and you can target the exact resist you need and get more resist per piece of jewelry. <p>-K<br><br>
